# data-testid Convention

## Pattern

```
data-testid="domain.component.element-type"
```

All three segments are **required**. Use kebab-case within each segment. Separate segments with `.`.

| Segment | Description | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `domain` | Feature area or route domain | `auth`, `nav`, `employees`, `incidents`, `reporting` |
| `component` | The specific component or form within that domain | `login-form`, `sidebar`, `list`, `detail`, `edit-form` |
| `element-type` | What the element is and/or does | `email-input`, `submit-btn`, `table`, `error-message`, `back-btn` |

## Rules

- **Stable**: never derived from dynamic content (no IDs, indices, user-generated strings)
- **Unique**: the full three-part string must be unique within the domain
- **Consistent element suffixes**: use `‑btn` for buttons, `‑input` for text/number/date inputs, `‑select` for dropdowns, `‑table` for tables, `‑link` for navigation anchors/router-links, `‑message` for inline feedback, `‑dialog` for modals
- **Framework-agnostic**: the same convention applies to Vue, React, and Angular repos; copy this rule verbatim
- **Bindings**: prefer static literals (`data-testid="..."`) in templates. Bindings (`:data-testid`) are acceptable only when the value is a fixed string from static config (e.g. `navItems.ts`). The rendered DOM value must still be stable and match the registered test ID. Bindings that incorporate runtime or user data are forbidden.

## Examples

```html
<!-- Auth -->
<input data-testid="auth.login-form.email-input" />
<button data-testid="auth.login-form.sign-in-btn" />
<span data-testid="auth.login-form.error-message" />
<button data-testid="auth.forgot-password-form.submit-btn" />

<!-- Navigation -->
<a data-testid="nav.sidebar.home-link" />
<a data-testid="nav.sidebar.logout-btn" />

<!-- Navigation via static config (e.g. navItems.ts) — binding OK -->
<RouterLink :data-testid="item.testId" /> <!-- item.testId is a fixed string in navItems.ts -->

<!-- Employees feature -->
<button data-testid="employees.list.add-btn" />
<table data-testid="employees.list.table" />
<button data-testid="employees.list.delete-btn" />
<button data-testid="employees.detail.edit-btn" />
<span data-testid="employees.detail.name" />
<button data-testid="employees.edit-form.cancel-btn" />
```

## In Page Object Models (Playwright)

Reference test IDs using the full dot-notation string:

```ts
this.emailInput = page.getByTestId('auth.login-form.email-input')
this.submitButton = page.getByTestId('auth.login-form.sign-in-btn')
```

## Do Not

- Use the old flat kebab-case format: ~~`data-testid="email-input"`~~
- Embed dynamic values: ~~`data-testid="`employee-${uid}`"`~~ or ~~`:data-testid="\`employee-${uid}-delete-btn\`"`~~
- Bind runtime or user data: ~~`:data-testid="item.id"`~~, ~~`:data-testid="index"`~~
- Omit any of the three segments: ~~`data-testid="login.email-input"`~~
- Use underscores or camelCase: ~~`data-testid="auth.loginForm.emailInput"`~~

